TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hanley, Kathleen Weiss
AU  - Hoberg, Gerard
T1  - The Information Content of IPO Prospectuses
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq024
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 23
IS  - 7
SP  - 2821
EP  - 2864
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using word content analysis, we decompose information in the initial public offering prospectus into its standard and informative components. Greater informative content, as a proxy for premarket due diligence, results in more accurate offer prices and less underpricing, because it decreases the issuing firm’s reliance on bookbuilding to price the issue. The opposite is true for standard content. Greater content from high reputation underwriters and issuing firm managers, through Management’s Discussion and Analysis, contribute to the informativeness of the prospectus. Our results suggest that premarket due diligence and disclosure by underwriters and issuers can serve as a substitute for costly bookbuilding. 
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq024
ER  - 



